         <abstract>
            <p>We study the numerical properties of the equations of motion of constrained systems derived with Dirac brackets. This formulation is compared with one based on the extended Hamiltonian. As concrete examples, a pendulum in Cartesian coordinates and a chain molecule are treated.</p>
          </abstract>
